Show HN: Stackjoy – a language agnostic code generator
text:
This is an example tutorial on how to use Stackjoy to quickly generate customizable components for an Angular codebase.

We have been using Stackjoy as independent contractors for a while but it was always just a bunch of code glued together to serve our own needs. A few months ago we decided to make it more ready for a wider audience. We’re not yet fully there but we’re at a point where we can start showing what it can do. It was built with Angular so we’re starting with Angular generators…in fact, we used Stackjoy to build Stackjoy.

It may not be something you’d use now for your software development but we have many more ready-to-use examples coming. Stackjoy is language agnostic so it works for any programming language.

If it is something you could see yourself using we’d really appreciate your feedback. Even if it’s not, we’d appreciate your feedback too so we can better understand why and hopefully we can address it in the future.

Lastly, if you have any suggestion for code generators you’d like to see, we are happy to hear about it and put it on our list.

Show HN: JukeLab – a DIY jukebox for your party
text:
JukeLab is a music player app that simulates a classic jukebox.

First, curate a Spotify playlist of 100 albums, then load it into the JukeLab app to see it displayed like a jukebox.

Then you and your friends can browse through the album artwork, find your favorite album and song, and add it to the queue by entering a four digit code.

JukeLab is truly unique when you set it up as dedicated tablet with a physical number pad. This experience feels just like an old-school jukebox in a bar, and invites people to interact with and converse about the music all night.

The magic is in curation and participation.

The app is written in Flutter, which has been great for a hobbyist to write once and release it on web, iOS and Android simultaneously. I run it on a Kindle Fire and a USB keypad which can be found for $75 total.

You can see a demo in your browser here. It will prompt for a Spotify login when you select your first track:

https://www.getjukelab.com/j/jukelab-101
